<div class='container my-4'>
  <h1 class='text-center mb-4'>Tips for Growing a Vegetable Garden</h1>
  <div class='row mb-4'>
    <div class='col-md-6'>
      <div class='card' style='border: 1px solid #dcdcdc;'>
        <div class='card-body'>
          <h5 class='card-title'>Essential Tips and Techniques</h5>
          <ul class='list-unstyled'>
            <li><strong>Choose the Right Location:</strong>
              Ensure your garden gets at least 6-8 hours of sunlight daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Prepare Your Soil:</strong>
              Enrich the soil with compost or well-rotted manure to improve fertility.</li>
            <li><strong>Water Wisely:</strong>
              Water plants early in the morning to reduce evaporation and disease.</li>
            <li><strong>Mulch Your Garden:</strong>
              Use mulch to retain soil moisture and suppress weeds.</li>
            <li><strong>Rotate Crops:</strong>
              Change the location of your plants each year to prevent soil depletion and reduce pest
              problems.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class='col-md-6'>
      <div class='card' style='border: 1px solid #dcdcdc;'>
        <div class='card-body'>
          <h5 class='card-title'>Environmental Benefits</h5>
          <ul class='list-unstyled'>
            <li><strong>Reduces Carbon Footprint:</strong>
              Growing your own vegetables reduces the need for transportation and packaging.</li>
            <li><strong>Conserves Water:</strong>
              Home gardens often use rainwater and greywater, reducing the demand on local water
              supplies.</li>
            <li><strong>Enhances Biodiversity:</strong>
              Gardens support various forms of life, from insects to birds, contributing to local
              ecosystems.</li>
            <li><strong>Improves Air Quality:</strong>
              Plants help to absorb pollutants and produce oxygen, leading to cleaner air.</li>
            <li><strong>Promotes Soil Health:</strong>
              Organic gardening practices improve soil structure and prevent erosion.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
